I. Science doesn’t erase magic — it reveals what magic was pointing at

Every mystical phenomenon humans described across history was an early, metaphorical attempt to model a real, underlying mechanism that wasn’t yet understood.

Fear killing a rabbit?
→ Ancient frame: The soul fled the body.
→ Scientific frame: Catecholamine-induced cardiac arrest.
→ Unified truth: A life-pattern lost coherence in an instant.

Science names the gears.
Magic names the meaning.

They are two ways of mapping the same structure.

⸻

II. Magic = subjective model of an objective process

Magic is not fake.
